  * fixed assets.svg in gtk2 dark (#2817)

  [ Chris Billington ]
  * Add scalable/ui folder to index.theme (#2831)

  [ Elsie Hupp ]
  * @elsiehupp (#2835)
  * Add symbolic Snap app and mimetype icons (#2845)

  [ Frederik Feichtmeier ]
  * Gtk3 theme: remove firefox border axing (#2869)
  * Gtk3 Nautilus list view change (#2881)
  * GtkTheme: monochrome spinners and orange links (#2883)
  * ShellTheme: update to orange link colors (#2884)
  * GtkThemes: revert to upstreams app notifications (#2886)
  * Gtk4Theme: remove outdated tweaks (#2890)
  * Gtk4: yaru upstream sync with tweak fixes (#2901)
  * Remove "yaru-light" and keep "yaru" as the fully light theme (#2922)
  * Gnome-software: remove css except green counter (#2942)

  [ benni3-1415 ]
  * Simpler cursor shape & Updated spinner colors (#2868)

  [ Linux Lovin' Llama ]
  * workspace-placeholder instead of dash-placeholder (#2891)

  [ Marco Trevisan (Treviño) ]
  * meson: Bump upstream version to 21.10.1
  * debian/control: Update breaks on gnome-shell 40
  * debian/control: Bump dependency on mutter 0.51
  * debian/control: Use debhelper 13
  * debian/yaru-theme-gnome-shell.alternatives: Use dh_installalternatives.
    And switch to new alternative name (gdm-theme.gresource) as previous is
    not supported by gnome-shell >= 40. The shell will also care about
    removing all the gdm3-theme.gresource alternatives so we don't have to
    handle that here.
  * debian/yaru-theme-gtk.install: Do not install Yaru-light themes anymore
    They are not provided anymore as per commit 37c779.
    There's only one yaru now.
  * debian: Add migration script to migrate users from Yaru-light to Yaru.
    We use session-migration through dh-migrations in d/control
  * gnome-shell/dock: Update theme to follow dash-to-dock changes
  * gnome-shell-theme.gresource.xml: Use gdm.css as stylesheet

 -- Marco Trevisan (Treviño) <marco@ubuntu.com>  Wed, 07 Jul 2021 09:01:50 +0200

