yaru-theme (20.04.3) focal; urgency=medium

  [ Carlo Lobrano ]
  * shell: re-use silver color for mouse selection
  * light themes: slightly brighten up shell and gtk popovers
  * nautilus: use destructive color for "stop loading" floating button
    (Fixes: #1980)
  * gtk: update assets for new color palette (Fixes: #1730)
  * switch: stronger disabled state in default and light variants
    (Fixes: #2016)
  * shell: use straight tile-preview corners
  * headerbar: white outline for suggested-action button (Fixes: #2019)
  * apps/nautilus: make infobar more visible (Fixes: #1989)
  * shell: use the same gtk style for slider borders
  * build/shell: symlink shell variants to alternate theme directory for
    theme selection (Fixes: #2043)
  * Reduce differences between default and dark variant headerbar buttons

  [ Jupiter007 ]
  * Remove input gaming legacy
  * Improve full colour audio-speakers icon
  * Legacy 16px *-remove.svg icons pixel perfect (#2087)
  * Fix twisted paths in legacy 16px svgs (#2085)

  [ Feichtmeier ]
  * Tweaks.scss: notebook tab improvements
  * Shell theme upstream fixes (LP: #1865563)
  * Shell theme: Provide a Yaru process-working asset
  * Gtk3: headerbar button fixes
  * Adapt gtk2 to gtk3
  * Gtk3: Make level bars green that aren't low
  * ShellTheme: colorize app grid rename dialog label
  * Change shell spinner from blue to #f7f7f7
  * Fix headerbar button regression caused by #2010
  * Dark gt3k theme: darken $borders_color by 2%
  * Clean up third party app styling
  * Gtk3: darken progressbar border colors
  * headerbar: fix missing states in suggested button outline
  * Provide application health, preferences-desktop and system-shutdown icons
  * Update software-update-available icon
